{#-
  HLRs.md.j2 — Jinja2 template for the High-Level Requirements document.

  Owns ALL standard scaffolding: H1 title, version/date/author block,
  per-section H2 headings, per-requirement bullet shape, and the
  "*Trace:*" footer. Project-specific content comes from the <hlrs>
  payload of doc/Project.xml.

  Data shape (see tools/Project_xml_README.md for the full schema):

      project.metadata.{title,version,date,author}
      project.name           — long project name
      project.short_name     — short project name
      project.hlrs           — list of <section> objects, each:
          .number            — section number (string)
          .title             — section title
          .intro             — markdown intro paragraph (may be empty)
          .hlrs              — list of <hlr> objects:
              .id            — e.g. "HLR-001"
              .name          — short title (becomes the bold lead-in)
              .text          — markdown body (verbatim)
              .traces        — list of <trace target ref/> SimpleNamespaces

  Trace rendering: each <trace target="SDD" ref="X.Y"/> renders as
  "[SDD.md §X.Y](SDD.md)". The XML schema does not currently carry
  GitHub anchors or section titles, so the link target is the bare
  document. Extend the schema if richer trace links are needed.
-#}
{%- macro render_trace(tr) -%}
{%- if tr.target == "SDD" -%}
[SDD.md §{{ tr.ref }}](SDD.md)
{%- elif tr.target == "HLR" -%}
[{{ tr.ref }}](HLRs.md){% if tr.name %} ({{ tr.name }}){% endif %}
{%- elif tr.target == "LLR" -%}
[{{ tr.ref }}](LLRs.md)
{%- else -%}
{{ tr.target }} {{ tr.ref }}
{%- endif -%}
{%- endmacro -%}
# {{ project.metadata.title }}

**Version:** {{ project.metadata.version }}
**Date:** {{ project.metadata.date }}
**Author(s):** {{ project.metadata.author }}

{% for sec in project.hlrs %}
## {{ sec.number }}. {{ sec.title }}

{% if sec.intro %}{{ sec.intro }}

{% endif -%}
{% for hlr in sec.hlrs %}
*   <a id="{{ hlr.id }}"></a>**{{ hlr.id }}: {{ hlr.name }}.**
    {{ hlr.text | indent(4) }}
{% if hlr.traces %}    *Trace:* {% for tr in hlr.traces %}{{ render_trace(tr) }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}.
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
{% endfor -%}
